class Solution {
    public int[] transformArray(int[] nums) {
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            nums[i] = nums[i] % 2;
        }
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        return nums;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution replaces each number in the array with its remainder when divided by 2, effectively replacing even numbers with 0 and odd numbers with 1, then sorts the array in non-decreasing order.

